title: Independent candidate Nadeem Qureshi wins PP-217 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Muhammad Nadeem Qureshi has won the election for Punjab Assembly constituency PP-217, Multan-V by securing 62,204 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Pakistan Muslim League (N) candidate, Sheikh Muhammad Tariq Rasheed, who bagged 32,091 votes.
Overall votersâ€™ turn-out remained 41.56%.
